The National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Senator Abdullahi Adamu, has assured that the party will recover its stolen mandate from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Benue State in the forthcoming governorship election. He, therefore, tasked the leadership of the party in the state to ensure that they recovered what he referred to as the party’s stolen mandate. He made the remark yesterday during the official flag-off of the APC’s “Alialization Alia/Ode’’ 2023 gubernatorial campaign in Gboko LGA of the state. Adamu added through his National APC Vice Chairman, North Central, Alhaji Mu’azu Bawa Rijau, that, “APC is Benue and Benue is APC and with the loyalty of Benue people to APC, capped with the landmark achievements recorded by President Muhammadu Buhari’s administration, APC mandate, which he said was stolen in 2015, must return to APC in 2023.” Senate: Adamu, Kyari, Nasiha’s seats still vacant 9 months after resignation Buhari congratulates Senate President Ahmad Lawan at 64 Also, the minister of Special Duties and Inter-Governmental Affairs, Senator George Akume, said the plot to frustrate the election of the APC presidential candidate, Bola Ahmed Tinubu and Kashim Shettima, using the Muslim-Muslim issue, will not succeed. 